.SH NAME
bb-pr-comment - Add a comment to a pull request


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbb pr comment  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Add a comment to a pull request using --body, --body-file, or --body-file - for stdin. This first pass is intentionally deterministic for agent and script usage. Use the comment subcommands to view, edit, delete, resolve, or reopen specific pull request comments.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--body\fP=""
	Comment body text

.PP
\fB--body-file\fP=""
	Read the comment body from a file, or '-' for stdin

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for comment

.PP
\fB--host\fP=""
	Bitbucket host to use

.PP
\fB--jq\fP=""
	Filter JSON output using a jq expression

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=""]
	Output JSON with the specified comma-separated fields, or '*' for all fields

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	Bitbucket repository target as , /, or a repository URL

.PP
\fB--workspace\fP=""
	Optional workspace slug used only to disambiguate a bare repository target


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Do not prompt for missing input, even in an interactive terminal


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bb pr comment 1 --body 'Looks good'
  bb pr comment 1 --repo workspace-slug/repo-slug --body-file comment.md
  printf 'Ship it\\n' | bb pr comment https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/1 --body-file - --json
.EE


